    {
      "num": 2,
      "name": "Power Engine",
      "weeks": "Weeks 6–10",
      "startDate": "2026-07-18",
      "endDate": "2026-08-22",
      "focuses": [
        "Turn that new strength into fast, explosive movement.",
        "Keep stripping body fat while protecting hard-earned muscle."
      ],
      "message": {
        "paragraphs": [
          "Cycle 1 built more than you think. Your Lat Pulldown went 26 to 33 kilograms, your leg curl jumped 60 percent, and in fifteen sessions you never once reported pain. That's a base. What the logs also show: the barbell lifts sat still — your last squat session was an RPE 6, which means the weight on the bar was lighter than the athlete under it. This cycle fixes that.",
          "Power Engine has two jobs. First, teach your body to move fast — jumps, bounds, throws, and a new kind of pressing where the legs launch the weight. This is what \"more fast in padel\" is actually made of. Second, march the barbell lifts up on a schedule. Every primary lift now has a written weekly target. The bar goes up because the plan says so, not when it feels like a good day.",
          "Three days. Denser, sharper, built around your padel week. By the end of these five weeks the first step, the smash, and the numbers on the bar will all say the same thing: faster and stronger than the athlete who finished Cycle 1."
        ],
        "outcomes": [
          "Squat at 35 kg+ moving fast — up from a stuck 20",
          "Deadlift and hip thrust progressing every single week",
          "First cycle of true ballistic pressing completed",
          "Continuous lateral bounds — spring, land, spring again",
          "All three days trained, every week — no dead zones",
          "Rotational throws visibly faster by week five"
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "num": 3,
      "name": "Athlete Sculpt",
      "weeks": "Weeks 11–15",
      "focuses": [
        "Sharpen power, speed, and on-court agility.",
        "Dial in the lean, defined look — including visible abs."
      ],
      "teaser": {
        "paragraphs": [
          "Cycle 3 is called Athlete Sculpt, and the name is literal. The strength you build now and the speed you sharpen here become the raw material — Cycle 3 carves it into the fastest, leanest version of you this programme has seen. The agility work gets court-specific. The definition work gets visible. But none of it can be carved from soft stone — the density gets built here first.",
          "Earn the sculpt."
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "num": 4,
      "name": "Peak & Polish",
      "weeks": "Weeks 16–20",
      "focuses": [
        "Bring everything together — strength, speed, and conditioning.",
        "Look and move like the athlete you've been building toward."
      ]
    }
  ],
